
Android Button
Let's learn how to perform event handling on button click.
// Find the Button view by its ID
val button: Button = findViewById(R.id.button)

// Set an OnClickListener to handle button clicks
button.setOnClickListener {
    // Perform an action when the button is clicked
    Toast.makeText(applicationContext, "Button clicked", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show()
}

Android Toast
Displays information for the short/long duration of time and then it disappears
   toastbtn.setOnClickListener{
   Toast.makeText(this, "Hello Javatpoint", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show()
   }

Custom Toast
We are able to customize the toast, such as we can display image on the toast
use fancy toast or custom toast from github
copy the dependencies and add in gradle file and sync it
now use it

